verbs.description: [V: planned] [ARG1: parenthood] launches plan to protect abortion access planned parenthood on wednesday launched a campaign to protect access to abortion as widely as possible even if the supreme court with the addition of conservative justice brett kavanaugh moves to curtail a woman right to undergo the procedure we know that we 'll need an ironclad network of states and providers across the country where abortion will still be legal and accessible no matter what happens at the supreme court said dawn laguens planned parenthood executive vice president brett kavanaugh abortion roe supreme court donald trump supreme court of canada president donald trump seattle
